SQL Interview Syllabus (3 Years Experience)

1. Fundamentals (Must be perfect)
----------------------------------
Topics

SELECT, WHERE, DISTINCT
ORDER BY, LIMIT
Basic filtering (AND, OR, IN, BETWEEN, LIKE)
NULL handling

Questions

Find all employees with salary > 5000.
Get unique departments from Employee table.
Find employees whose name starts with 'A'.
Get top 5 highest salaries.
Find employees where commission is NULL.
2. Joins (Core Interview Area)

Topics

INNER JOIN, LEFT JOIN, RIGHT JOIN
SELF JOIN
CROSS JOIN (conceptual)

Questions

Get employee name with department name.
Find employees who don’t have a department.
Find departments with no employees.
Get manager name for each employee (self join).
Find pairs of employees working in same department.
3. Aggregation & GROUP BY

Topics

COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX
GROUP BY
HAVING

Questions

Count employees per department.
Find average salary per department.
Get departments having more than 3 employees.
Find highest salary in each department.
Find total salary per department.
4. Subqueries (Very Important)

Topics

Scalar subquery
Correlated subquery
IN, EXISTS

Questions

Find employees earning more than average salary.
Get employees working in same department as 'A'.
Find second highest salary using subquery.
Get employees whose salary is greater than their manager.
Find departments with highest average salary.
5. Window Functions (Highly Important for 3+ yrs)

Topics

ROW_NUMBER()
RANK(), DENSE_RANK()
PARTITION BY
LEAD(), LAG()

Questions

Assign row numbers to employees by salary.
Find top 3 salaries per department.
Find second highest salary per department.
Compare current salary with previous employee.
Find salary difference between employees.
6. Advanced Aggregation

Topics

CASE WHEN
Conditional aggregation

Questions

Count employees with salary > 5000 per department.
Find male vs female employee count.
Get departments where average salary > overall avg.
Pivot salary ranges (0–5k, 5k–10k, etc.).
Count employees hired each year.
7. Data Modification

Topics

INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE
MERGE (important in real projects)

Questions

Update salary by 10% for IT employees.
Delete employees with no department.
Insert data from one table to another.
Merge two employee tables.
Update manager_id using another table.
8. Indexing & Performance (Interview Differentiator)

Topics

Index types
Query optimization basics
Execution plan (conceptual)

Questions

Why is a query slow on large data?
When to use index?
Difference between clustered vs non-clustered index.
How to optimize JOIN query?
What is query execution plan?
9. Constraints & Keys

Topics

PRIMARY KEY, FOREIGN KEY
UNIQUE, NOT NULL
DEFAULT

Questions

Difference between PRIMARY KEY and UNIQUE.
What happens if foreign key is violated?
Can a table have multiple UNIQUE keys?
Explain cascading delete.
Design table with constraints.